summary: it’s weird how what they did with nat/clint feels so much like a no-homo.  and how much (rewatching ultron) my reactions to it...
body:
it’s weird how what they did with nat/clint feels so much like a no-homo. 

and how much (rewatching ultron) my reactions to it are the same. 

and also how much they mirror the effects of The No-Homo Ploy on fandom: that is, hate/ignore the woman. But she actually has some really good points and says some really interesting things? And though I think Nat/Clint is a really important relationship to acknowledge but don’t actually care whether it’s romantic/sexual or not - and while I hate their insistence on shoving the heteronormativity thing of Nat/Bruce (seriously, they even do the ‘beauty taming the beast’ thing, ugh) - neither of these provide any reason to disapprove of The Secret Marriage Of Clint, or to blame it on the woman.

And yet that’s automatically what I find myself doing, as a watcher. 

Do better, me.

title: Always (Bucky x OFC) Part 3/12
body:
My Masterlist

Part 1 Part 2

It was Bucky’s last night before shipping out, and Emilia felt sick to her stomach.

But she had promised she would go to the expo with Steve and Bucky, Bucky having found dates for himself and Steve while Emilia finally agreed to go with the man from the pharmacy down the street.

It had started out alright to begin with, until Steve walked away from his date and Emilia had chased after him to find out what was wrong.  After a short argument with him, he had stormed off and Emilia returned to the crowd to see her date a little too close to Steve’s date.

She had rolled her eyes and turned to walk away, only to run straight into Bucky’s chest, who grinned down at her, his eyes crinkling until he saw her expression.  Looking over her head, he saw her date dancing with the girl and scowled.

“I’ll take care of him,” he muttered, but Emilia grabbed his arm, pulling him back and murmuring that he wasn’t worth it. “He’s a loser,” he replied. “He doesn’t see what’s right in front of him. I’ll make sure he does.”

“Don’t worry about it,” she said, not sparing another glance over her shoulder. “The last thing you need is to get in trouble right before you ship out. It isn’t worth it.” She began to pull the pins from her hair, but he stopped her. “I just wish I hadn’t gotten all dressed up for nothin.”

Her long, dark blonde hair was curled and pinned up in a bun, a few strays had broken loose to frame her face, which she pushed out of the way.  Her dress was a dark navy blue, white polka dots sprinkled all over as it hugged her body tightly.  It was new.  She pushed the stray hairs out of the way again as she let out a sigh and Bucky shook his head.

“You look perfect, Doll,” he said as he wrapped his arm around her shoulders, and pulled her close, “Dance with me.”

She rolled her eyes, “What about your date?”

“I leave tomorrow, let me have one more dance with my favorite Doll.”  He smiled down at her and she sighed.

“One dance,” she relented, letting him guide her towards the throng of people.

Once they were slowly swaying to the music, Bucky gave her his toothy grin and pulled her close, “I’m gonna miss you, Doll,” he said quietly.  “Who’s gonna keep me in check without you around?”

“Probably your commanding officer,” she replied, letting her head fall forward to rest on his chest.  “I’m gonna miss you too, Buck.  Come back home to us, okay?” She looked up into his eyes to see them crinkled at the corners as he continued to smile down at her.  “Come back home to me.”

“Always, Em,” he replied softly.  “I’ll always come back to you.”

She let her head rest on his shoulder again as they swayed back and forth, his arms around her waist and hers wrapped around his slim shoulders.

He had spent too much time around Steve growing up, letting some of his personality traits rub off on him, but never the good ones, just the bad.

“You and Steve are such punks,” she said quietly.  “So self-sacrificial, never thinking about the ones who care about you.”

He squeezed her tightly, “M‘sorry, Doll.”

“You are not,” she said immediately.  “But I wouldn’t have you any other way.”

-

One dance turned into two, and then three, and before Emilia knew it it was two in the morning and Bucky was walking her back to her shared apartment with Steve.  She assumed Steve was already home and asleep, so she quietly trudged up the stairs with Bucky behind her.

“Be safe out there, okay?” she said quietly as she turned around to say goodbye. “Be safe and come home to us in one piece.”  She smiled up at him as tears began to prick her eyes and he pulled her in for a tight hug.  “Write, stay in touch, and please stay as safe as possible.”

“Like I said earlier, Em,” he replied, still holding her tightly.  “I’ll always come back to you.”

She smiled up at him as he released her and raised herself on her tiptoes to kiss his cheek lightly. “Give ‘em hell, Buck.  I’ll see you when you come home.”

He grinned again, nodding as she turned to open the door and step inside.

Part 4

Her long, dark blonde hair was curled and pinned up in a bun, a few strays had broken loose to frame her face, which she pushed out of the way.  Her dress was a dark navy blue, white polka dots sprinkled all over as it hugged her body tightly.  It was new.  She pushed the stray hairs out of the way again as she let out a sigh and Bucky shook his head.

“You look perfect, Doll,” he said as he wrapped his arm around her shoulders, and pulled her close, “Dance with me.”

She rolled her eyes, “What about your date?”

“I leave tomorrow, let me have one more dance with my favorite Doll.”  He smiled down at her and she sighed.

“One dance,” she relented, letting him guide her towards the throng of people.

Once they were slowly swaying to the music, Bucky gave her his toothy grin and pulled her close, “I’m gonna miss you, Doll,” he said quietly.  “Who’s gonna keep me in check without you around?”

“Probably your commanding officer,” she replied, letting her head fall forward to rest on his chest.  “I’m gonna miss you too, Buck.  Come back home to us, okay?” She looked up into his eyes to see them crinkled at the corners as he continued to smile down at her.  “Come back home to me.”

“Always, Em,” he replied softly.  “I’ll always come back to you.”

She let her head rest on his shoulder again as they swayed back and forth, his arms around her waist and hers wrapped around his slim shoulders.

He had spent too much time around Steve growing up, letting some of his personality traits rub off on him, but never the good ones, just the bad.

“You and Steve are such punks,” she said quietly.  “So self-sacrificial, never thinking about the ones who care about you.”

He squeezed her tightly, “M‘sorry, Doll.”

“You are not,” she said immediately.  “But I wouldn’t have you any other way.”

-

One dance turned into two, and then three, and before Emilia knew it it was two in the morning and Bucky was walking her back to her shared apartment with Steve.  She assumed Steve was already home and asleep, so she quietly trudged up the stairs with Bucky behind her.

“Be safe out there, okay?” she said quietly as she turned around to say goodbye. “Be safe and come home to us in one piece.”  She smiled up at him as tears began to prick her eyes and he pulled her in for a tight hug.  “Write, stay in touch, and please stay as safe as possible.”

“Like I said earlier, Em,” he replied, still holding her tightly.  “I’ll always come back to you.”

She smiled up at him as he released her and raised herself on her tiptoes to kiss his cheek lightly. “Give ‘em hell, Buck.  I’ll see you when you come home.”

He grinned again, nodding as she turned to open the door and step inside.

Part 4
